        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-blue-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span><span><strong>Always check parallels first:</strong> Before playing perpendicular to existing words, check if a parallel play scores more. Parallels often score 30-50% higher than you'd expect.</span></li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-blue-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span><span><strong>High-value tiles need premium squares:</strong> Never play J, Q, X, or Z without hitting at least a DLS. These tiles on blank squares waste 50-70% of their potential value.</span></li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-blue-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span><span><strong>Open multiple lanes simultaneously:</strong> One threat is easy to block. Three simultaneous threats overwhelm your opponent's defensive resources. Create scoring opportunities in different board areas.</span></li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-blue-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span><span><strong>Play through tiles quickly:</strong> The more tiles you see, the more scoring opportunities you find. Play 4+ tiles per turn. Don't sit on a rack hoping for miracles — cycle and draw fresh.</span></li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-blue-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span><span><strong>Use hooks aggressively:</strong> Add S to an opponent's word to form your own word simultaneously. CATS becomes SCATS if you play SCATS through their CAT — scoring your full word plus the hook bonus.</span></li>
      </ul>

